# Scaffold joelclaw-api

## Question

Stand up `joelhooks/joelclaw-api` per the [charter](./charter-joelclaw-api.svx): jj-colocated repo at `~/Code/joelhooks/joelclaw-api`; Bun + `bun test`; tsgo (TS 7) typechecking with tsc fallback wired in CI-style check script; effect-smol (Effect v4); XState v5; ultracite with its ox presets (oxlint/oxfmt underneath — verify the preset wiring actually exists in current ultracite and record the config); Effect HttpApi skeleton with one health endpoint served via Bun/Hono on a fixed port (pick and record it); service bearer token leased from agent-secrets; `.agent_sources/github.com/{Effect-TS/effect, statelyai/xstate, honojs/hono}` cloned read-only with an AGENTS.md that mandates inspecting them before non-trivial edits (copy the joelclaw-central convention). No Convex content yet — custody transfer is the next task. Resolved when `bun test` and the typecheck pass, the health endpoint answers on localhost, and the resolution records port, package name, and any stack substitutions forced by reality (e.g. tsgo or ultracite-ox not actually workable today — record what was swapped and why, loudly).

## Answer

Resolved 2026-07-13 (pi worker Hangdog Verence, steering-verified: bun test 3 pass, DECISIONS.md reviewed). Repo live at `~/Code/joelhooks/joelclaw-api` (jj colocated): Bun 1.3.14, health endpoint on **:4200**, XState v5 health machine, `.agent_sources` archives (effect/xstate/hono) + AGENTS.md doctrine, `JOELCLAW_API_TOKEN` bearer stub with /health exempt. Reality-checked substitutions (full detail in the repo's `DECISIONS.md`): `effect-smol` is not an npm package → `effect@4.0.0-beta.98` (the actual v4 line); Effect v4 beta has no `HttpApi` builder yet → contract lives in Effect Schema served by Hono, explicitly temporary; **ultracite 7.9.3 does ship Oxlint/Oxfmt presets** (Joel was right) — `oxlint.config.ts`/`oxfmt.config.ts` extend Ultracite over Oxc; tsgo (TS7 native preview) typechecks clean with tsc fallback wired.
